    <descript>
      <abstract>This polygon coverage uses a single line to represent the County boundary.</abstract>
      <purpose>The County coverage may be used as a background theme to provide contrast and proportion to other features which do not cover the extent of the County.</purpose>
      <supplinf>
    An annotation subclass has been created to label Arlington County and surrounding jurisdictions. ANNO.JURIS100 is intended for plotting at 1" = 100' scale (same as the mapbook) and identifies jurisdictions in every map sheet, which crosses the County boundary. 

    Associated shapefiles:  
    CNTYLN - county boundary
    CNTYUSGS - local USGS quad polygons, divided by county lines
    USGSSHTS - outline of 4 local USGS quad sheets
   </supplinf>
    </descript>
